rical context, dealing with the word as introduced by Destutt de Tracy in 1798 and looking both forward and backward at such enquirers in the field as Aristotle, Bacon, Locke, Rousseau, Marx, Karl Mannheim, and Leo Strauss. The volume presents original and provocative insights into the meanings and uses of ideology, as well as into specific "ideologies." The essays will be of importance to students of philosophy and sociology of knowledge, political scientists, and historians.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aIdeologyvCongresses. 0aIdeologyxCongresses. 0aIdées politiquesxCongrès. 0aIdéologiexCongrès. 0aPhilosophyxCongressesxPolitical aspects. 0aPhilosophyxPolitical aspectsvCongresses. 0aPolitical sciencexCongressesxPhilosophy. 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophyvCongresses. 0aSpanish dramaxHistory and criticism. 0aTheaterzSpainxHistory. 4aPhilosophy. 4aPolitical Science. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978088920654040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889206540423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889206540/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles